    "description": "<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Longer and more powerful than blaster rifles, these weapons are for large-scale actions, often supplementing ground squads and providing cover for artillery gunners while their weapons are being set up. These weapons are normally about one to oneand-a-half meters long, and can be run off power packs or attached to generators for unlimited firepower. They are normally available only to the military, but sometimes the odd smuggler, pirate, or bounty hunter manages to &ldquo;acquire&rdquo; one through less than legal means.</span></p>\n<p><strong><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Generator rules:&nbsp;</span></strong><span style=\"font-family: var(--font-primary); font-size: var(--font-size-14);\">Normally, the repeating blaster requires a second </span><span style=\"font-family: var(--font-primary); font-size: var(--font-size-14);\">crewman to regulate the weapon&rsquo;s power generator; this second </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"font-family: var(--font-primary); font-size: var(--font-size-14);\">crewman must make an Easy </span><span class=\"fontstyle2\" style=\"font-family: var(--font-primary); font-size: var(--font-size-14);\"><em>blaster: repeating blaster</em> </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"font-family: var(--font-primary); font-size: var(--font-size-14);\">skill </span><span style=\"font-family: var(--font-primary); font-size: var(--font-size-14);\">while adjacent to the weapon to regulate its power. After you </span><span style=\"font-family: var(--font-primary); font-size: var(--font-size-14);\">regulate the repeating blaster&rsquo;s power, it will function </span><span style=\"font-family: var(--font-primary); font-size: var(--font-size-14);\">normally until the beginning of your next turn. If the weapon&rsquo;s </span><span style=\"font-family: var(--font-primary); font-size: var(--font-size-14);\">power is not regulated (that is, if a second crewman has not </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">done so or failed his skill roll), apply a -1D penalty on all attack rolls made with the weapon.</span> </p>\n<p><strong><span class=\"fontstyle4\">Type: </span></strong><span class=\"fontstyle5\">Light repeating blaster</span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle4\"><strong>Scale:</strong> </span><span class=\"fontstyle5\">Character</span></p>\n<p><strong><span class=\"fontstyle4\">Skill: </span></strong><em><span class=\"fontstyle6\">Blaster: Repeating Blaster</span></em></p>\n<p><strong><span class=\"fontstyle4\">Ammo: </span></strong><span class=\"fontstyle5\">25 or Power generator only</span></p>\n<p><strong><span class=\"fontstyle4\">Cost: </span></strong><span class=\"fontstyle5\">2,000 (power packs: 25)</span></p>\n<p><strong><span class=\"fontstyle4\">Availability: </span></strong><span class=\"fontstyle5\">2, X</span></p>\n<p><strong><span class=\"fontstyle4\">Fire Rate: </span></strong><span class=\"fontstyle5\">1</span></p>\n<p><strong><span class=\"fontstyle4\">Range: </span></strong><span class=\"fontstyle5\">3-50/120/300</span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle4\"><strong>Damage:</strong> </span><span class=\"fontstyle5\">6D</span> <br style=\"font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; line-height: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: -webkit-auto; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-size-adjust: auto; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px;\" /><br /></p>",
